subject: Correct license information
commitMessage:
Correct license information

Change the license field to spdx-compliant identifier.
Use %license macro to install license files.

Change-Id: Ibde2a85a8692c58e0be7ff15b8b5b1054e382f84
Signed-off-by: Juhyeon Yun <juhyeon.yun@samsung.com>

comments.message: Uploaded patch set 1.
Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This is closer to truth than the commit message in https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/#/c/17954 but not still not precise. Personally I would write:

  Correct license information

  Change the license field to spdx-compliant identifier.
  Use %license macro to install license files.

Please read the following pages and follow the guidelines for writing
commit message contained therein.

* http://bit.ly/goodcommitmessages
* http://who-t.blogspot.com/2009/12/on-commit-messages.html
* http://dep.debian.net/deps/dep3/
* https://wiki.tizen.org/wiki/Talk:Packaging/Guidelines
Uploaded patch set 2.

Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(1 comment)

That's better now. However, there is still a small issue in the commit message. Please see the in-line comment.
Uploaded patch set 3.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Looks great.
Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1
Patch Set 3: Verified+1
Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
